lead_paragraph: Supporters of a medical marijuana constitutional amendment in Florida say they have collected enough voter signatures to put their proposal on the November ballot, joining a growing list of states revisiting drug laws.

headline.main: Florida Medical Marijuana Campaign Says It Has Signatures for Ballot
